1
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,240
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

2
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:27,570
♪Always stumbling upon
my little secrets♪

3
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:31,990
♪Falling on my brows, my lashes,
even the strands by my mouth♪

4
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:36,660
♪Like my favorite kitten
on a rainy spring afternoon♪

5
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

6
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:45,110
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:49,450
♪Hitting all my little thoughts,
my doubts, and my temper♪

8
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:54,300
♪Like my favorite beer and fried chicken
in autumn, or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

9
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,770
♪Why is it you again?
That sweet way you speak♪

10
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,080
♪As if the whole world knows
my mind is full of you♪

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,530
♪Why is it still you?
That secret smile behind your cool facade♪

12
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:11,760
♪I might as well play along.
Let me protect you♪

13
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:16,190
♪Why is it always you?
The smile at the corner of your lips♪

14
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:20,590
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

15
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:33,220
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

16
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:34,040
=Love Has Fireworks=

17
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:34,861
(Based on "Investment Men and Women"
by Hong Er on Jinjiang Literature City)

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 6=

19
00:01:38,350 --> 00:01:39,120
What do you mean?

20
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:42,430
Did you poison the food?

21
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:44,310
No, no!

22
00:01:45,150 --> 00:01:47,000
No, that's not it.

23
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,070
Seriously, no. I swear.

24
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,150
I swear there's no poison.

25
00:01:49,590 --> 00:01:50,920
No, it's just that I wanted

26
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,040
to ask if you'd
help me revise my research report.

27
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:53,560
Please?

28
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:55,950
The research report?

29
00:01:59,070 --> 00:02:00,070
You scared me to death.

30
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:03,350
You finished it already?

31
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,590
Yeah. But it's not polished enough.

32
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:06,430
I was thinking,

33
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,288
since you're one of the people in charge

34
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:09,910
of Shanlifang's IPO project,

35
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,360
if you could give me some feedback,

36
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:12,310
that'd be perfect.

37
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,120
I get it now.

38
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,840
You're trying to use this report

39
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,910
to win Fang Yun over.

40
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,030
Exactly.

41
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,120
Well, that's a pretty big favor.

42
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:26,630
A huge one.

43
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,150
One meal isn't enough for that.

44
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:34,080
Unless...

45
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,870
Unless what?

46
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,840
You want a rent discount?

47
00:02:37,844 --> 00:02:39,555
A hundred yuan is the best I can do.

48
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,400
You think I'm like you?

49
00:02:41,910 --> 00:02:42,910
Money grubber.

50
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:47,560
Unless you call me "master"
with full sincerity.

51
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,280
What? What's that? Don't want to?

52
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:59,310
Haven't you heard the story?

53
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:02,180
In ancient times, someone would become
another person's student

54
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,560
just for correcting a single word.

55
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,280
You're so unwilling to learn.

56
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,630
No, that's not what I mean.

57
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,960
I'm just saying,

58
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:12,030
I don't know
if your advice is any good yet.

59
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,630
You're doubting me?

60
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,960
Fine.

61
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:21,680
I'll put my talents to lesser use

62
00:03:21,711 --> 00:03:22,720
and check it out for you.

63
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:23,560
Bring it over.

64
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,710
Really? One second.

65
00:03:34,488 --> 00:03:37,400
(In-Depth Report on Shanlifang Hotel)
Here. Review it properly.

66
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:50,500
(In-Depth Report on Shanlifang Hotel.
Enhance Layout and Prepare for IPO)

67
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:02,750
What's with that expression?

68
00:04:02,777 --> 00:04:04,800
Your eyebrows are
all scrunched together.

69
00:04:05,711 --> 00:04:06,800
Is it really that bad?

70
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,200
Seriously?

71
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,520
Can you let me focus on the report?

72
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,560
At least say something.

73
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,733
Be quiet for a minute
and let me go through it properly.

74
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,600
Take your time.

75
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:31,240
Is it really that bad?

76
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:55,810
♪There's no need
to know the ending from the start♪

77
00:04:57,930 --> 00:05:03,180
♪Let the melody play through the chords
with the wind♪

78
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:10,610
♪There's no need
to keep every promise from the past♪

79
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:19,010
♪Leave some surprises
for the unknown in life♪

80
00:05:20,140 --> 00:05:21,030
(Zhao De)

81
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:25,380
♪There's no need
to force things between two people♪

82
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:27,680
Hello?

83
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:32,000
I figured out how to deal
with Shanlifang now.

84
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,950
Just carry on with the team's work.

85
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,240
Leave the rest to me.

86
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:39,430
Okay.

87
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:48,880
♪A hug means more
than countless apologies♪

88
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:52,210
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

89
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:56,550
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

90
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,780
♪A quiet shoulder♪

91
00:05:58,780 --> 00:06:02,780
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

92
00:06:02,790 --> 00:06:03,680
How is it?

93
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,190
Not bad.

94
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,870
I knew there couldn't be
anything seriously wrong with it.

95
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:08,870
That's not true.

96
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,920
There are a lot of places
that need work.

97
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:12,560
Tell me.

98
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:17,270
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

99
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:17,800
Look here.

100
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,680
Shanlifang Hotel Group's

101
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,866
marketing positioning shows
obvious differentiation,

102
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,177
so there's no direct competition
within the industry.

103
00:06:27,770 --> 00:06:28,500
See that?

104
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:32,480
You're amazing, Master.

105
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,800
Calling me "master" already?
Didn't hesitate at all.

106
00:06:37,177 --> 00:06:38,680
When it comes to research reports,

107
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:39,920
you really are my master.

108
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,177
But if we're talking about
taking me as your apprentice,

109
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:43,200
you have a long way to go.

110
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,120
You're biting the hands that feed?

111
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,560
No, not at all.

112
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,040
I'll cook for you. You pick the day.

113
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:51,240
Now that's more like it.

114
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,750
This part needs to be changed, too?

115
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,488
Of course.

116
00:06:55,822 --> 00:06:58,777
I've been talking about it for ages.
What have you been writing down?

117
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,320
Are you not going to bed?

118
00:07:14,955 --> 00:07:16,333
I'll sleep after I finish this.

119
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:20,140
Well,

120
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,740
you have strong execution skills.

121
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:24,860
But I'm curious.

122
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,620
If you'd always been like this,

123
00:07:28,088 --> 00:07:29,520
you wouldn't have spent so many years

124
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,977
stuck at the same position.

125
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:32,860
I was silly.

126
00:07:32,977 --> 00:07:34,260
For the sake of the so-called home

127
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:35,900
and the so-called
fair resource allocation,

128
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:37,390
I passed up a lot of opportunities.

129
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,288
Cut that out.

130
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,460
Stop flattering yourself.

131
00:07:42,444 --> 00:07:44,220
I've heard those kinds of excuses
many times.

132
00:07:44,377 --> 00:07:46,450
Did someone hold a gun to your head
and force you

133
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:48,100
to make those decisions?

134
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:50,700
People say things like that
when they want

135
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,780
to avoid competition
and stay in their comfort zone.

136
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:55,220
They're just making excuses
for themselves.

137
00:08:01,244 --> 00:08:03,666
I've realized that you're
pretty interesting sometimes.

138
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:04,300
How so?

139
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,740
Most girls after a breakup

140
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:09,300
cry and make a scene.

141
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:11,420
But you act as if nothing happened.

142
00:08:13,222 --> 00:08:15,850
Is it because you'd been together
so long that the feelings faded?

143
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:18,444
Or because after the breakup,
you realized it wasn't a big deal?

144
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:19,420
Wrong.

145
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:22,700
The longer you're together,
the deeper the bond becomes.

146
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:24,820
Even if the romance fades,

147
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,100
family and friendship get mixed into it.

148
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:29,900
The kind of love

149
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:32,580
hurts like being torn into pieces.

150
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:37,020
I didn't get that impression from you.

151
00:08:39,977 --> 00:08:42,777
Do I have to break down and cry
for it to count as heartbreak?

152
00:08:42,866 --> 00:08:44,733
Do you think I have time
to be heartbroken?

153
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,300
Is the report finished?

154
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,420
Have I found a job?

155
00:08:47,940 --> 00:08:49,260
Have I paid off my loan?

156
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:50,980
That person

157
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,940
was the biggest flaw in my life plan.

158
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,660
Now that it's fixed,

159
00:08:56,100 --> 00:08:57,100
he's no longer needed.

160
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,420
Done!

161
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:34,340
Thank you, Li Yifei.

162
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:01,420
You're up.

163
00:10:01,511 --> 00:10:03,555
I've got to head out.
Help yourself to breakfast.

164
00:10:03,711 --> 00:10:04,580
Where are you going?

165
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:06,060
A date.

166
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:07,860
With who?

167
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,020
Guess.

168
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:09,820
I'm not guessing.

169
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:10,980
Come on, guess.

170
00:10:11,288 --> 00:10:12,140
Just tell me.

171
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:16,020
Besides Qian Fei and Dang Yu,

172
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:18,020
who else would I be meeting?

173
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:20,460
Qian Fei and Dang Yu?

174
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:21,900
That doesn't sound right.

175
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:26,220
You're meeting your lover, aren't you?

176
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,100
Otherwise,

177
00:10:28,180 --> 00:10:30,980
why aren't you wearing your ring today?

178
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:35,580
Come on,

179
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:36,980
you're reading way too much into it.

180
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:38,300
I knew you'd ask that.

181
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:40,060
Think about it.

182
00:10:40,060 --> 00:10:41,380
Fei just got dumped.

183
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:43,140
And I'm waving a giant diamond ring

184
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:45,020
in front of her face.

185
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,140
Would that be appropriate?

186
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:58,690
(Grand Chancellor:
Po Ming, my level is low right now.)

187
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,430
(It's because I accidentally
gave away all my gear.)

188
00:11:00,444 --> 00:11:01,690
(You know what I'm capable of.)

189
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,150
(You can check out
my recent battle record.)

190
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,790
(Please give me a chance
to join the team.)

191
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:10,300
(Po Ming)

192
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,500
Cheng, whatever you're doing,

193
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:22,900
you need to eat.

194
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:24,660
I'm not eating.

195
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:25,820
Leave me alone.

196
00:11:39,780 --> 00:11:42,140
(Po Ming)

197
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,300
I'll make a toast.

198
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:52,700
We're gathered here today

199
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:54,260
to celebrate our bestie

200
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:56,380
moving into her new home
and dumping her ex.

201
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:56,700
Yes!

202
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:57,990
To a brand-new chapter in life!

203
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:58,540
Cheers.

204
00:11:58,660 --> 00:11:59,220
Cheers.

205
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:03,460
I'm so hungry.

206
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:06,180
You sure are in a hurry.

207
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:07,540
How could I not be?

208
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:09,780
We've been waiting for you
before starting dinner.

209
00:12:09,940 --> 00:12:10,500
You're hungry?

210
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,660
Alright. Have this meat.

211
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:14,940
Hot.

212
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:19,340
Have some more.

213
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:23,380
Yu, you eat like a horse.

214
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:25,020
Your appetite is a little scary.

215
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:28,900
If you worked as much as I do,

216
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,000
you'd eat this much too.

217
00:12:31,688 --> 00:12:33,660
Are you really planning to go back
to Hejing?

218
00:12:34,140 --> 00:12:34,780
Yes.

219
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:37,020
It's not just about the money.

220
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:38,740
I want to prove what I'm capable of.

221
00:12:38,977 --> 00:12:40,933
I don't want to stay in
my comfort zone anymore.

222
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:42,540
You're really going all in on this?

223
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:44,760
There are plenty of firms
in the industry besides Hejing.

224
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:46,620
Hejing is the industry benchmark.

225
00:12:47,420 --> 00:12:47,900
Exactly.

226
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:50,260
Also, I don't have
any front-office experience.

227
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:51,460
If I can work under Ms. Fang,

228
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:53,155
I can avoid a lot
of unnecessary detours.

229
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,180
But if you join her project team,

230
00:12:57,222 --> 00:12:59,377
you'll be working on
the Shanlifang project.

231
00:13:00,422 --> 00:13:01,777
What's the problem with that?

232
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:07,620
Are you worried things will get awkward

233
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,933
if I'm on the same project
as that person in the room?

234
00:13:09,977 --> 00:13:11,533
And that people will start talking?

235
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:14,780
Yeah. I told you before.

236
00:13:15,180 --> 00:13:16,900
If people in the office find out,

237
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,540
they'll make up all kinds of stories.

238
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:20,060
There's no need to worry.

239
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:21,580
I have nothing to hide.

240
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:22,940
There's nothing between us.

241
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:24,860
It's not about that.

242
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:27,580
You need to be careful, anyway.
Don't tell anyone.

243
00:13:28,177 --> 00:13:30,044
I'm not bringing any of them back here.

244
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:34,540
(Finance Department, Wang Ruohai Resume)

245
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:40,340
(Shanlifang Group Personnel File,
Wang Ruohai)

246
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:43,100
(Strange.)

247
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:46,780
(Her ex works at Shanlifang.)

248
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,500
(Doesn't she know?)

249
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:52,380
(Probably not.)

250
00:13:52,688 --> 00:13:54,430
(Otherwise, she wouldn't be
so eager to join)

251
00:13:54,444 --> 00:13:55,622
(Fang Yun's project team.)

252
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,740
(Which means she's about to see)

253
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:01,620
(her ex and his new girlfriend
every single day.)

254
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:02,660
(Shanlifang Finance Director)

255
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:05,140
(On top of that, she'll have to
listen to everything they say)

256
00:14:05,155 --> 00:14:06,288
(because they're the clients.)

257
00:14:09,088 --> 00:14:10,660
(I can't even bear to think about it.)

258
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:32,180
Here you go, Fei's Fragrance.

259
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:34,420
This looks great.

260
00:14:36,688 --> 00:14:38,260
Someone's been texting you nonstop.

261
00:14:38,288 --> 00:14:39,400
Are you not going to reply?

262
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,060
Check it for me. It's my alt account.

263
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,822
There are a lot of messages.

264
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,430
(Grand Chancellor: It was a man-made
disaster! Save me!)

265
00:14:49,444 --> 00:14:51,230
(Just give me a chance.
I'll do anything!)

266
00:14:51,244 --> 00:14:53,660
(Saving a life
is a great merit, Po Ming.)

267
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:54,900
Read them yourself.

268
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:59,220
When is he going to stop?

269
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,660
Ignore him. Just some weirdo.

270
00:15:01,820 --> 00:15:03,100
You've got an admirer?

271
00:15:03,977 --> 00:15:05,111
What admirer?

272
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,511
The guy I told you about before.
He wants to join the team.

273
00:15:07,577 --> 00:15:08,333
Grand Chancellor.

274
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,420
Po Ming? Po Ming bro?

275
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,860
He thinks you're a guy.

276
00:15:14,260 --> 00:15:15,780
That's exactly the point.

277
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:16,460
I never reveal

278
00:15:16,460 --> 00:15:18,220
any personal information online.

279
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,511
He's sent you so many messages.

280
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:20,500
You won't even reply?

281
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:21,500
Poor thing.

282
00:15:22,222 --> 00:15:23,380
You're too soft-hearted.

283
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:25,700
Alright. For your sake.

284
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,860
I'll send him a few replies.

285
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,780
Cheers.

286
00:15:33,460 --> 00:15:34,780
(Po Ming)
(Are you a minor?)

287
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,660
(Focus on your studies.)

288
00:15:36,666 --> 00:15:39,100
(Grand Chancellor)
(I'm an adult. And I'm really reliable.)

289
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:41,220
(If you don't believe me, test me.)

290
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,755
(Po Ming)
(No time.)

291
00:15:44,311 --> 00:15:45,900
(Grand Chancellor)
(Can I be a backup?)

292
00:15:47,244 --> 00:15:48,180
(Po Ming)
(A backup?)

293
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:50,460
(Our team doesn't run into
emergencies very often.)

294
00:15:50,488 --> 00:15:52,622
(A backup doesn't stand much
of a chance.)

295
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:53,990
(Grand Chancellor)
(That's okay.)

296
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:56,355
(I can be a backup and help out
with whatever you need.)

297
00:15:57,466 --> 00:15:58,900
(You sure have a lot of free time.)

298
00:15:59,155 --> 00:16:01,311
(Grand Chancellor)
(As long as I can help the team.)

299
00:16:01,380 --> 00:16:02,580
(I'd even give up sleep.)

300
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:10,220
(Po Ming)
(Keep your word.)

301
00:16:10,422 --> 00:16:12,511
(Don't complain later
that I work you too hard.)

302
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,900
(Grand Chancellor)
(No problem!)

303
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:14,820
(Mister Po Ming,)

304
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,340
(just leave it to me.)

305
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:35,933
(Grand Chancellor)

306
00:16:35,955 --> 00:16:39,220
(Supreme War Saint Grand Chancellor)

307
00:16:40,780 --> 00:16:42,860
Alright, we'll leave Jingjing
to your care now.

308
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:45,580
Don't worry.
I'll get her home safe and sound.

309
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:46,780
Even though

310
00:16:46,780 --> 00:16:48,700
I'll never be able to compete
with her besties

311
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,240
for the chance to have dinner with her.

312
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:52,020
Oh, stop it. Spare me the pity party.

313
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,180
Once I get onto
the Shanlifang project team,

314
00:16:54,244 --> 00:16:55,644
we'll have a proper celebration.

315
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,460
Plus-ones are allowed.

316
00:16:57,620 --> 00:16:58,140
Shanlifang?

317
00:16:58,140 --> 00:16:59,380
We'll all go together then.

318
00:16:59,980 --> 00:17:00,700
We're leaving.

319
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,555
Let's do it together.

320
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:03,990
Alright. Stop being
lovey-dovey in front of me.

321
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,890
Have you lost your mind?

322
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:05,700
Get going.

323
00:17:05,780 --> 00:17:06,180
We're off.

324
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:06,740
We're leaving.

325
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:07,560
- We're off.
- Bye.

326
00:17:07,577 --> 00:17:08,488
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

327
00:17:17,780 --> 00:17:19,180
I should get going, too.

328
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,300
You keep the liquor.

329
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:21,940
So many of them.
I can't finish them all.

330
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,700
We'll drink them next time.

331
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,420
(Regarding Shanlifang's Pre-IPO...)

332
00:17:28,860 --> 00:17:30,380
Keep it safe.

333
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,300
I know.

334
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:48,260
What are you doing here?

335
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:51,140
Can't I come to my bestie's for dinner?

336
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:53,900
Oh, right. You're Fei's
landlady's bestie.

337
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,300
Are you here for Li Yifei?

338
00:17:56,555 --> 00:17:57,980
You're not drunk this time, are you?

339
00:17:58,711 --> 00:17:59,580
I haven't had a drop.

340
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:00,900
Good.

341
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,300
Get home early.

342
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:04,900
By the way...

343
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:09,060
I'm Jun Cheng.

344
00:18:09,620 --> 00:18:11,020
I don't know your name yet.

345
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:12,820
I'm Dang Yu.

346
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:14,300
Dang Yu.

347
00:18:15,580 --> 00:18:17,700
I'm sorry about last time.

348
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:20,940
It's fine. I was just
messing with you at the bar.

349
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:21,820
No need to apologize.

350
00:18:21,977 --> 00:18:23,140
I threw you to the ground too.

351
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:24,820
Let's call it even.

352
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:28,540
Alright. I'll treat you
to a meal sometime.

353
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:31,260
No need. I'm usually pretty busy.

354
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,420
Don't get me wrong.

355
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:34,260
What I mean is

356
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,340
you're Qian Fei's bestie,

357
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:38,620
and Yifei is my buddy.

358
00:18:39,140 --> 00:18:39,740
If you think

359
00:18:39,740 --> 00:18:41,533
it'd be awkward for us
to have dinner alone,

360
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,860
we can invite them along.

361
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,820
You're pretty sincere.

362
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:49,140
Alright. When I have time.

363
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:49,860
I'll text you.

364
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:50,940
Sure.

365
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:51,580
Bye.

366
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,300
I'll wait for your message.

367
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:04,740
Wait. She never gave me her WeChat.

368
00:19:17,380 --> 00:19:19,740
Does Qian Fei still have no idea

369
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:21,940
that Wang Ruohai has joined Shanlifang?

370
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:23,460
No.

371
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:26,020
You should tell her.

372
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:27,700
Think about what she's going to face.

373
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:29,220
Her cheating ex-boyfriend.

374
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:30,940
His current girlfriend,

375
00:19:31,022 --> 00:19:32,580
who happens to be Shanlifang's heiress.

376
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:35,340
What a mess.

377
00:19:36,420 --> 00:19:38,300
What a disaster.

378
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:43,220
Do you want her to get into
the project team or not?

379
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,820
Do you think

380
00:20:03,260 --> 00:20:05,060
she actually wants to
have dinner with me,

381
00:20:05,444 --> 00:20:06,860
or was she brushing me off?

382
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,740
I'm talking to you. Don't ignore me.

383
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:13,940
Neither.

384
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:15,940
What is it then?

385
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:20,100
She couldn't even be bothered
to brush you off.

386
00:20:26,380 --> 00:20:28,260
No way. I need your help.

387
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:30,460
How?

388
00:20:30,820 --> 00:20:33,420
At least get her contact number for me.

389
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:37,860
Don't tell me you've fallen for her?

390
00:20:40,220 --> 00:20:42,420
I don't know if it's love or not.

391
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:44,220
I just feel like

392
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,840
she's different from everyone else.

393
00:20:46,140 --> 00:20:47,260
Different how?

394
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:50,180
Think about it.

395
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:52,540
One second

396
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:54,460
she's a cute, petite girl,

397
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,660
and the next, bam.

398
00:20:56,755 --> 00:20:58,060
She throws me flat on the ground.

399
00:20:58,420 --> 00:20:59,460
That's cool.

400
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:04,260
Are you a masochist or what?

401
00:21:07,060 --> 00:21:08,180
I don't think so.

402
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,380
Anyway, I feel like

403
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:12,140
there are a lot of different sides
to her.

404
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:14,380
I want to get to know her better.

405
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:18,460
All I know is she's Qian Fei's colleague

406
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:20,260
at Hejing Securities.

407
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:21,300
Anything else?

408
00:21:21,422 --> 00:21:23,700
That's it. You'll have
to find out the rest yourself.

409
00:21:24,380 --> 00:21:25,700
No.

410
00:21:25,700 --> 00:21:28,460
Ask your landlady for me.

411
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:32,340
Do I look like the gossiping type?

412
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,180
Fair enough.

413
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:41,300
You're a rich, handsome guy
who dates supermodels.

414
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:43,933
Of course, you wouldn't understand
the misery of us single folks.

415
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:49,220
Oh, you broke up.

416
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:50,780
I forgot. Sorry.

417
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,260
Honestly, you don't look heartbroken.

418
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:53,820
In fact,

419
00:21:54,955 --> 00:21:56,244
you've put on a little weight.

420
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:58,700
No way!

421
00:21:58,780 --> 00:21:59,222
It's true.

422
00:22:15,260 --> 00:22:16,780
I did put on some weight.

423
00:22:18,380 --> 00:22:20,100
I can't keep eating
the landlady's cooking.

424
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:25,420
The landlady cooks for you?

425
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:28,420
Li Yifei!

426
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,900
Now I know why you're radiating
even after a breakup.

427
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:32,900
You've got someone now.

428
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:33,980
Typical you.

429
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:35,700
Don't be ridiculous.

430
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:36,900
Take a good look at her.

431
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:38,511
Do you really think she's my type?

432
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:39,780
If she's not your type,

433
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:41,044
why are you still living here?

434
00:22:41,088 --> 00:22:43,420
Didn't you say
Gui Lili rented this place

435
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:44,220
and you hated it?

436
00:22:45,020 --> 00:22:47,060
I'd have to have the money to move out.

437
00:22:47,511 --> 00:22:48,540
If you want to move out,

438
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:50,780
there are ten thousand ways to do so.

439
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:52,380
But there's only one reason

440
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:53,780
to stay.

441
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:57,700
Talk to the hand.

442
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:03,860
(Shanghai World Financial Center)

443
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:11,460
Don't worry.

444
00:24:11,460 --> 00:24:13,820
The report is on your idol's desk now.

445
00:24:13,888 --> 00:24:15,500
Just sit tight and wait for a response.

446
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,060
(Thanks, Yu.)

447
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:50,940
I'm back.

448
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,500
Why are you eating that?

449
00:25:14,940 --> 00:25:15,820
What are you doing?

450
00:25:17,340 --> 00:25:18,340
Listen.

451
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:20,340
No one in this house
is allowed to eat junk food.

452
00:25:21,866 --> 00:25:22,980
You're not the landlord here.

453
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:24,500
Why should I follow your rules?

454
00:25:24,666 --> 00:25:26,060
We're sharing this apartment.

455
00:25:26,060 --> 00:25:27,340
We should have some consideration.

456
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:28,790
You're eating something that smells

457
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:29,844
so strong. It's making me

458
00:25:30,580 --> 00:25:31,100
sick.

459
00:25:32,100 --> 00:25:33,580
I'll eat it in my room then.

460
00:25:34,155 --> 00:25:35,940
So anything goes
as long as it's in your room?

461
00:25:36,060 --> 00:25:37,540
Then can I smoke in my room too?

462
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:38,700
That's not the same thing.

463
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:41,100
You smoke one cigarette,
and the smell won't go away all day.

464
00:25:41,220 --> 00:25:42,020
I can still smell it.

465
00:25:42,140 --> 00:25:43,180
Same logic.

466
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:44,700
If I can't smoke in my room,

467
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:46,860
you shouldn't eat instant noodles
in yours.

468
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:50,060
That's my dinner. Come on.

469
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,580
I'll order takeout for dinner.

470
00:25:53,510 --> 00:25:56,222
Takeout and instant noodles.
I'm not even sure which one's worse.

471
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:58,700
Don't you worry.

472
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,140
The food I order

473
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:04,260
will be delicious, safe,

474
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,780
and nutritionally balanced.

475
00:26:14,820 --> 00:26:15,740
How much is all this?

476
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:18,140
None of your business.

477
00:26:18,260 --> 00:26:19,660
I'm not asking you to pay for it.

478
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:23,700
I'm not trying to take advantage of you.

479
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:25,300
You threw my dinner away,

480
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:26,180
so I had no choice.

481
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:26,700
Fine.

482
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:28,940
Enough talking. Just eat.

483
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:30,980
I won't hold back then.

484
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:32,940
Thanks for the meal.

485
00:26:41,060 --> 00:26:42,420
What have you been busy with today

486
00:26:42,533 --> 00:26:44,022
that you didn't have time to cook?

487
00:26:46,220 --> 00:26:47,540
I submitted the report,

488
00:26:47,755 --> 00:26:49,220
but it's only scratching the surface.

489
00:26:49,955 --> 00:26:51,600
There's a lot more going on
at Shanlifang.

490
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:52,900
I need to dig deeper.

491
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:56,620
You're proactive.

492
00:26:57,044 --> 00:26:58,620
Did Fang Yun agree to reinstate you?

493
00:26:59,140 --> 00:26:59,940
Not yet.

494
00:27:00,380 --> 00:27:02,100
But it never hurts to be prepared.

495
00:27:04,980 --> 00:27:06,020
It's been a while.

496
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:07,140
How come there's no news?

497
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:10,340
I only handed in the report yesterday.

498
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:12,100
It's only been a day. No rush.

499
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:15,020
Knowing Fang Yun,

500
00:27:15,533 --> 00:27:17,100
do you think she'd put off today's work

501
00:27:17,100 --> 00:27:18,180
until tomorrow?

502
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:22,500
Something must've gone wrong.

503
00:27:24,866 --> 00:27:26,311
Yu works at the front desk.

504
00:27:26,377 --> 00:27:28,860
She bent the rules by putting
the report on Fang Yun's desk.

505
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,260
I can't ask her to do more.

506
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:32,540
No. It'll affect her job.

507
00:27:32,580 --> 00:27:34,820
You should hand it to Fang Yun yourself.

508
00:27:35,266 --> 00:27:37,220
Don't tell me
you don't have the guts for that.

509
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:39,500
It's not that I don't have the guts.

510
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:40,700
I just think

511
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:42,940
the quality of my work

512
00:27:43,020 --> 00:27:44,580
should speak for itself.

513
00:27:44,688 --> 00:27:46,288
I shouldn't have to do anything else.

514
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:49,140
If work performance
were all that mattered,

515
00:27:49,260 --> 00:27:51,780
you wouldn't have been laid off. Get it?

516
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:55,020
You sound like you know me pretty well.

517
00:27:55,222 --> 00:27:56,511
After reading your report,

518
00:27:56,580 --> 00:27:57,780
I got to know you a little.

519
00:27:58,140 --> 00:27:59,540
So what you're saying is

520
00:27:59,540 --> 00:28:00,820
you recognize my abilities?

521
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:02,100
I guess so.

522
00:28:02,620 --> 00:28:04,660
Seeing how pitiful you are
and having lost your job,

523
00:28:05,222 --> 00:28:07,133
I couldn't help
feeling a little sorry for you.

524
00:28:07,177 --> 00:28:08,340
So I figured I'd comfort you.

525
00:28:08,740 --> 00:28:09,980
I don't need your sympathy.

526
00:28:10,380 --> 00:28:11,060
I, Qian Fei,

527
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:12,980
will prove it to all of you.

528
00:28:19,220 --> 00:28:20,420
This shrimp is good. Try some.

529
00:28:20,666 --> 00:28:23,060
Didn't you say it wasn't nutritious?
That it was junk food.

530
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:25,540
Delicious junk food.

531
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:27,800
But it's not as good
as your stir-fried eggplant strips.

532
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:58,980
(Shanghai World Financial Center)

533
00:29:09,580 --> 00:29:10,500
Ms. Fang.

534
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:13,180
This is the research report
I prepared on Shanlifang.

535
00:29:13,266 --> 00:29:14,060
I also left a copy

536
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:15,940
on your desk before.

537
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:17,460
Maybe you've seen it.

538
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:19,380
I want to know
where exactly I fell short.

539
00:29:21,540 --> 00:29:22,540
You know how busy I am.

540
00:29:22,820 --> 00:29:24,140
I don't have the spare time

541
00:29:24,140 --> 00:29:25,460
to read an amateur piece.

542
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:26,980
But Ms. Fang,

543
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:29,340
all of my data analysis, observations,
and findings

544
00:29:29,620 --> 00:29:30,860
will definitely help

545
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:31,977
move your project forward.

546
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:33,380
I'm very confident about that.

547
00:29:37,980 --> 00:29:38,860
Satisfied now?

548
00:29:42,420 --> 00:29:43,140
A person

549
00:29:43,488 --> 00:29:44,600
may be very capable at work,

550
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:46,410
but without the company's recognition,

551
00:29:46,420 --> 00:29:48,500
they'll never get the chance
to show what they can do.

552
00:29:48,577 --> 00:29:51,619
A person who doesn't know how to cherish
will never be truly valuable.

553
00:29:51,620 --> 00:29:52,420
Do you understand?

554
00:30:12,340 --> 00:30:14,380
(Hejing Securities Co., Ltd.)

555
00:30:19,460 --> 00:30:22,420
Ms. Fang, I was worried
that Qian Fei might bother you,

556
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:24,460
so I took...

557
00:30:26,380 --> 00:30:28,220
Do you think my office is a place

558
00:30:28,220 --> 00:30:30,377
where anyone can walk in
and take whatever they want?

559
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:32,380
No, it's not that, Ms. Fang.

560
00:30:33,340 --> 00:30:34,420
I'm so sorry.

561
00:30:34,860 --> 00:30:36,540
I was wrong. It won't happen again.

562
00:30:37,260 --> 00:30:38,140
You can leave now.

563
00:31:05,060 --> 00:31:06,900
I'm hungry. Make dinner.

564
00:31:08,620 --> 00:31:10,622
The second I get home,
you start bossing me around.

565
00:31:10,630 --> 00:31:11,777
How very human of you.

566
00:31:12,260 --> 00:31:14,220
You owe me a meal. Forgot?

567
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:15,740
You promised.

568
00:31:15,740 --> 00:31:17,820
You could've told me in advance.

569
00:31:17,900 --> 00:31:19,844
There's nothing at home.
I can't cook anything.

570
00:31:20,540 --> 00:31:21,820
Says who?

571
00:31:22,044 --> 00:31:24,022
I bought the groceries.
They're in the kitchen.

572
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:26,180
You actually bought groceries?

573
00:31:26,511 --> 00:31:28,780
Buy groceries on your phone.
One tap, home delivery.

574
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:30,850
You're living in modern times,
and you don't know this?

575
00:31:30,866 --> 00:31:31,911
Hurry up and cook.

576
00:31:33,620 --> 00:31:34,740
He actually bought them.

577
00:31:37,220 --> 00:31:38,780
Wonders never cease.

578
00:32:21,580 --> 00:32:24,220
Young master, dinner's ready.

579
00:32:31,660 --> 00:32:32,500
Can't he hear me?

580
00:32:39,860 --> 00:32:40,940
Had enough?

581
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,460
I was testing whether
this door is soundproof.

582
00:32:44,933 --> 00:32:46,500
When I want it to be, it's soundproof.

583
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:48,060
When I don't, it's not.

584
00:32:48,180 --> 00:32:49,288
Got a problem with that?

585
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:51,380
Not bad.

586
00:32:56,900 --> 00:32:57,740
You met Fang Yun?

587
00:33:00,822 --> 00:33:01,844
Things didn't go well?

588
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:17,780
Landlady,

589
00:33:18,780 --> 00:33:19,620
have you

590
00:33:20,260 --> 00:33:21,420
ever imagined

591
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:23,220
we'd be where we are now?

592
00:33:24,700 --> 00:33:25,700
Like what?

593
00:33:26,260 --> 00:33:28,420
Sitting here having a heart-to-heart?

594
00:33:30,820 --> 00:33:31,580
Never.

595
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:35,060
Not in a million years.

596
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:38,340
Because you were a total creep

597
00:33:38,980 --> 00:33:39,820
in my eyes.

598
00:33:40,260 --> 00:33:42,300
And you were a shrew in mine.

599
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:50,700
You know what?

600
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:52,860
You should be thankful

601
00:33:53,420 --> 00:33:54,540
for having been blessed

602
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:57,860
with such a handsome tenant.

603
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:00,860
Handsome? Let me see.

604
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:03,340
You need to look?

605
00:34:07,380 --> 00:34:08,460
Two eyes,

606
00:34:09,660 --> 00:34:10,740
one nose,

607
00:34:11,060 --> 00:34:12,020
and one mouth.

608
00:34:13,100 --> 00:34:13,980
Pretty handsome.

609
00:34:17,540 --> 00:34:19,380
But what's the use?

610
00:34:19,620 --> 00:34:21,220
Look at the way you conduct yourself.

611
00:34:23,533 --> 00:34:24,580
I'm really not impressed.

612
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:26,260
Honestly,

613
00:34:26,260 --> 00:34:27,380
look at the state you're in.

614
00:34:27,620 --> 00:34:29,780
Living with a roommate
and throwing money around.

615
00:34:31,020 --> 00:34:32,740
I really can't stand it.

616
00:34:33,711 --> 00:34:34,955
Nobody's asking you to care.

617
00:34:35,820 --> 00:34:36,540
That's exactly why

618
00:34:36,660 --> 00:34:38,980
you should move out as soon as possible.

619
00:34:39,060 --> 00:34:41,020
A single man and a single woman,
both unmarried,

620
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:42,780
living together
isn't exactly appropriate.

621
00:34:43,444 --> 00:34:44,540
I don't mean to interfere,

622
00:34:45,300 --> 00:34:46,900
but doesn't your dad live in Shanghai?

623
00:34:47,020 --> 00:34:48,220
Why don't you move back home?

624
00:34:48,380 --> 00:34:49,980
Why insist on staying out here?

625
00:34:50,666 --> 00:34:51,980
My dad and I don't see eye to eye.

626
00:34:53,140 --> 00:34:55,420
Nothing I did
was ever good enough for him.

627
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,620
Whenever I was unhappy,
whenever things went wrong,

628
00:35:00,900 --> 00:35:02,740
he'd probably be the happiest person.

629
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:06,620
How can that be?

630
00:35:07,700 --> 00:35:10,140
He's your father. You're family.

631
00:35:10,820 --> 00:35:11,780
Family?

632
00:35:12,460 --> 00:35:14,700
Let me tell you something.

633
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:19,820
Back when my mom was seriously ill

634
00:35:20,860 --> 00:35:22,060
and sinking fast,

635
00:35:23,420 --> 00:35:25,460
during the hardest, most painful time,

636
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:28,220
he was nowhere to be found.

637
00:35:30,900 --> 00:35:32,460
He left my mom and me all alone.

638
00:35:35,460 --> 00:35:37,340
Who knows whether he was out having fun

639
00:35:37,660 --> 00:35:38,780
or buried in work?

640
00:35:40,700 --> 00:35:41,820
Is that what you call family?

641
00:35:47,060 --> 00:35:47,780
Hey.

642
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:52,940
What's wrong? I'm fine.

643
00:35:54,060 --> 00:35:56,300
It's not you. It's me.

644
00:35:56,340 --> 00:35:57,990
I haven't even cried.
Why are you crying?

645
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:01,180
It's not you. It's me.

646
00:36:02,100 --> 00:36:02,820
What's wrong?

647
00:36:04,060 --> 00:36:05,900
Hearing you talk about your mom

648
00:36:06,620 --> 00:36:08,940
made me think of my mom.

649
00:36:13,420 --> 00:36:17,180
My mom used to tell me

650
00:36:17,860 --> 00:36:19,840
to study hard

651
00:36:19,850 --> 00:36:21,220
and get into a good university.

652
00:36:22,900 --> 00:36:24,260
And look at me now.

653
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:29,940
Look at what my life's become.

654
00:36:31,020 --> 00:36:33,260
If my mom were still alive,

655
00:36:33,620 --> 00:36:36,780
seeing me like this
would break her heart.

656
00:36:39,980 --> 00:36:41,500
I spent the best years of my life

657
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:43,740
falling in love.

658
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:45,900
I thought getting married
and owning a home

659
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:47,940
was the best of my life.

660
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:52,380
But fate had other plans.

661
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:57,420
I got dumped. I got laid off.

662
00:36:58,060 --> 00:37:00,340
And now I'm in deep debt.

663
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:03,260
If she knew about this,

664
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:05,300
I could imagine how upset she'd be.

665
00:37:09,820 --> 00:37:10,460
Landlady,

666
00:37:11,420 --> 00:37:12,220
that's life.

667
00:37:13,300 --> 00:37:14,620
It's no big deal.

668
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:17,820
There'll always be something.

669
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:28,700
Landlady. Qian Fei.

670
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:32,100
Seriously?

671
00:37:32,110 --> 00:37:33,670
How do you manage to pass out in seconds

672
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:34,780
every time you drink?

673
00:37:34,980 --> 00:37:36,060
How do you even do that?

674
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:48,088
Alright. Don't sleep out here.
You'll catch a cold.

675
00:37:48,380 --> 00:37:50,220
Come on. Get up.

676
00:37:54,688 --> 00:37:55,488
My goodness.

677
00:37:56,300 --> 00:37:58,020
Can you really not feel a thing?

678
00:37:59,540 --> 00:38:00,140
Come on.

679
00:38:02,820 --> 00:38:04,780
Up you get. Go back to bed.

680
00:38:06,300 --> 00:38:07,100
Don't sleep here.

681
00:38:14,620 --> 00:38:16,940
Fine, you win.

682
00:38:17,820 --> 00:38:19,060
I'll get you back tomorrow.

683
00:38:21,660 --> 00:38:22,180
Come on.

684
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,660
How did you get this wasted?

685
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,740
(No matter how I look at it,)

686
00:39:58,740 --> 00:40:00,620
(Fang Yun should've made a move by now.)

687
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:03,380
(Why hasn't she reacted at all?)

688
00:40:05,580 --> 00:40:06,820
(Looks like this won't work.)

689
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:09,780
(I'll have to take her on directly.)

690
00:40:26,844 --> 00:40:28,580
I'm in a hurry.
Let me use the mirror first.

691
00:40:28,733 --> 00:40:30,220
At least wait for your turn, will you?

692
00:40:30,220 --> 00:40:31,580
You don't have a job, alright?

693
00:40:31,580 --> 00:40:32,860
What did you just say?

694
00:40:32,860 --> 00:40:33,460
I'm in a hurry!

695
00:40:33,460 --> 00:40:34,020
I came first.

696
00:40:34,020 --> 00:40:35,266
You don't have to go to work.

697
00:40:43,555 --> 00:40:44,888
Why are you fighting me for it?

698
00:40:45,940 --> 00:40:47,060
I'm off. Bye.

699
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:50,155
What's so special about having a job?

700
00:40:57,180 --> 00:40:58,500
Ms. Fang wants to see me?

701
00:41:02,155 --> 00:41:04,740
This research report is written by
a former backend employee

702
00:41:04,740 --> 00:41:06,244
who has already left the company.

703
00:41:08,940 --> 00:41:10,580
I'm not bringing it out to make a point.

704
00:41:12,044 --> 00:41:13,900
I'm bringing it out
to make you feel ashamed.

705
00:41:16,180 --> 00:41:17,420
This is the most valuable piece

706
00:41:17,420 --> 00:41:19,460
I've read in the last two weeks.

707
00:41:19,900 --> 00:41:22,140
All of you investment banking elites
working under me,

708
00:41:22,620 --> 00:41:24,420
if you've got a shred
of professional pride,

709
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:26,540
you should take a hard look

710
00:41:26,540 --> 00:41:28,180
at the work you're doing.

711
00:41:28,180 --> 00:41:29,155
Can you do that?

712
00:41:31,540 --> 00:41:32,180
Xinyao.

713
00:41:34,740 --> 00:41:35,740
Make ten copies of this.

714
00:41:43,740 --> 00:41:44,420
Ms. Fang,

715
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:46,300
should we follow

716
00:41:46,300 --> 00:41:48,580
the direction of this report
and keep working on it...

717
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:50,020
Keep working on what?

718
00:41:50,220 --> 00:41:52,220
You want to end up unemployed
like she did?

719
00:41:55,022 --> 00:41:56,511
Don't you have your own judgment?

720
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,860
I'm telling you to integrate the ideas.

721
00:42:01,180 --> 00:42:03,700
Don't look so defeated
just because I criticized you a little.

722
00:42:04,377 --> 00:42:06,466
The people from Zhizhong
are about to arrive.

723
00:42:07,740 --> 00:42:09,580
Get your heads in the game.

724
00:42:10,066 --> 00:42:11,620
Since you don't have an appointment,

725
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:15,020
please leave your name
and contact information.

726
00:42:15,140 --> 00:42:17,355
When he gets back,
he'll get in touch with you.

727
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:24,900
(Hejing Securities Co., Ltd)

728
00:42:24,900 --> 00:42:25,740
(Meeting Room)

729
00:42:27,740 --> 00:42:28,760
You all see this, right?

730
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:29,740
The chart here

731
00:42:29,755 --> 00:42:32,140
(Shanlifang Hotel Group Market Share)
was compiled from my report

732
00:42:32,155 --> 00:42:33,900
and the reports you submitted.

733
00:42:34,340 --> 00:42:36,900
(Ms. Fang used the integrated analysis
from my report.)

734
00:42:37,380 --> 00:42:38,820
(Looks like she called me here)

735
00:42:39,020 --> 00:42:40,620
(to bring me onto the project team.)

736
00:42:45,540 --> 00:42:46,460
You're here.

737
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:49,340
Yeah. I'm back.

738
00:43:00,140 --> 00:43:00,580
Good.

739
00:43:01,100 --> 00:43:02,700
Mr. Li, shall we?

740
00:43:03,060 --> 00:43:03,420
Sure.

741
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,860
=Love Has Fireworks=
(Next Episode Preview)

742
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,540
(We Empowered the Future Together.
2018 Company Annual Dinner Report)

743
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:12,100
Annual dinner...

744
00:43:12,100 --> 00:43:14,380
From three years ago?

745
00:43:15,066 --> 00:43:16,320
Have you made up your mind?

746
00:43:17,300 --> 00:43:18,220
I'm going on vacation.

747
00:43:18,780 --> 00:43:19,320
Good.

748
00:43:19,540 --> 00:43:20,430
Have a good trip.

749
00:43:21,210 --> 00:43:21,960
See you.

750
00:43:22,710 --> 00:43:24,380
What's your name?

751
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:26,900
Xin Ba.

752
00:43:26,980 --> 00:43:28,060
Simba.

753
00:43:28,660 --> 00:43:30,160
I'm big boy, Li Yifei.

754
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:31,340
Let's get to know each other.

755
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:34,020
That's enough, big boy.

756
00:43:47,711 --> 00:43:52,071
♪There's no need
to know the ending from the start♪

757
00:43:54,411 --> 00:43:59,541
♪Let the melody play through the chords
with the wind♪

758
00:44:02,651 --> 00:44:06,861
♪There's no need
to keep every promise from the past♪

759
00:44:09,191 --> 00:44:15,181
♪Leave some surprises
for the unknown in life♪

760
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:22,311
♪There's no need
to force things between two people♪

761
00:44:23,981 --> 00:44:29,801
♪Perhaps I'll feel alone,
yet still find you there for me♪

762
00:44:32,041 --> 00:44:37,751
♪There's no need
to dwell on right or wrong, nor fear♪

763
00:44:38,681 --> 00:44:45,311
♪A hug means more
than countless apologies♪

764
00:44:45,531 --> 00:44:48,661
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

765
00:44:48,931 --> 00:44:52,811
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

766
00:44:53,481 --> 00:44:55,211
♪A quiet shoulder♪

767
00:44:55,211 --> 00:45:00,081
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

768
00:45:00,471 --> 00:45:03,451
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

769
00:45:03,681 --> 00:45:07,801
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

770
00:45:08,201 --> 00:45:10,291
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

771
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:14,201
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

772
00:45:14,941 --> 00:45:18,171
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

773
00:45:18,451 --> 00:45:22,681
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

774
00:45:23,051 --> 00:45:24,771
♪A quiet shoulder♪

775
00:45:24,771 --> 00:45:29,431
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

776
00:45:29,971 --> 00:45:32,951
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

777
00:45:33,131 --> 00:45:37,451
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

778
00:45:37,751 --> 00:45:40,721
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

779
00:45:41,581 --> 00:45:49,521
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪
